\t    `reward_pool_fundings` ordered by `created_at desc, id desc`. Default\n1927\t    limit `PEEK_REWARD_POOL_FUNDINGS_DEFAULT_LIMIT = 50`, max\n1928\t    `PEEK_REWARD_POOL_FUNDINGS_MAX_LIMIT = 250` — same clamp shape used by\n1929\t    the growth queries. Returns `{ id, roundId, feeLamports, fundedLamports,\n1930\t    createdAt }`; `roundId` is the `reward_pool_fundings.round_id` source\n1931\t    round so `/economy/rewards` can drill into the round that fed the pool.\n1932\t  - `getRewardsOverview({ sql, now, recentFundingsWindowHours })` — emits\n1933\t    one `PeekMetric` per `PeekRewardsOverviewMetricId`:\n1934\t    `rewards.balance_lamports`, `rewards.lifetime_funded_lamports`,\n1935\t    `rewards.lifetime_paid_lamports`, `rewards.recent_fundings`. Lamport\n1936\t    metrics keep the raw u64 string in `value` (FR-4 monetary precision),\n1937\t    use thousands-separator formatting in `valueDisplay`, and link to\n1938\t    `/economy/rewards#pool` / `/economy/rewards#fundings` for drill-down.\n1939\t    The recent-fundings window defaults to\n1940\t    `PEEK_REWARDS_RECENT_FUNDINGS_WINDOW_HOURS = 24` (clamped 1..720h) so\n1941\t    tests can override the window without touching wall-clock. Pool +\n1942\t    recent-fundings queries fire in parallel via `Promise.all` to keep\n1943\t    overview latency low.\n1944\t- New view-model types in `peek/src/lib/types/peek.ts`:\n1945\t  - `PeekRewardConfigExpectedType` — the value-type union\n1946\t    (`integer | float | ratio | lamports | unknown`).\n1947\t  - `PeekRewardConfigRow` — `{ key, value, updatedAt, definition,\n1948\t    expectedType }`. `definition` is `string | null` so unknown keys keep a\n1949\t    distinct visual treatment without faking a definition.\n1950\t  - `PeekRewardPool` — `{ balanceLamports, lifetimeFunded, lifetimePaid,\n1951\t    updatedAt }`. All lamport fields are `string` to round-trip u64.\n1952\t  - `PeekRewardPoolFundingRow` — `{ id, roundId, feeLamports,\n1953\t    fundedLamports, creat